[center][size=6][color=#ffff00][b]Relic Terminal Checklist[/b][/color][/size]
[size=4]An in-game UI checklist to track all 9 Relic Terminals.[/size][/center]

Made for by request, based on my [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/cyberpunk2077/mods/25594]Perk Shard Checklist[/url] mod.

This mod adds a simple, in-game UI to track all 9 Relic Terminals so you never have to alt-tab again.

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/WKUrfSX.gif[/img][/center]
[line]
[size=5][color=#ffff00][b]New in 3.0.0[/b][/color][/size]
[list]
[*][color=#e06666][b]New required dependency: 0-Engine.[/b][/color] This version will not run without it. See [b]Requirements[/b] below. Earlier versions did not need it.
[*][b]Rebuilt scanner:[/b] The proximity scanner now runs on 0-Engine. It reacts to you crossing into range instead of polling on a timer, so there is no CPU cost when you are away from any terminal and detection is tighter up close.
[*][b]Game's own relic marker:[/b] Terminals now use the game's native relic icon instead of a separate mod icon, and it shows up as soon as the terminal area loads in.
[*][b]Instant detection:[/b] A terminal is checked off the moment you finish the personal link.
[*][b]Retroactive tracking:[/b] Terminals you activated before installing now get checked off automatically once you are near them in Dogtown.
[/list]
[line]
[size=5][color=#ffff00][b]Features[/b][/color][/size]
[list]
[*][b]Automatic Tracking[/b]: Passively detects Relic Terminals as you play and checks them off once collected.
[*][b]In-Game Checklist[/b]: Track or view your progress on all 9 Terminals in Dogtown.
[*]Progress is saved automatically with your game save (per-character).
[*]A [b]Settings[/b] tab to configure the Proximity Scanner range and optional [b]Lazy Mode[/b].
[*]In-game descriptions, closest fast travel points, and location info for every terminal.
[*]A [b]Set Map Pin[/b] button to create a waypoint to the terminal's location.
[*]A [b]Teleport[/b] button (in Lazy Mode) to instantly teleport to the terminal.
[*]An [b]Unstuck[/b] button (in Lazy Mode) to teleport you to V's H10 apartment if you get stuck.
[*]A counter to see your total collected terminals.
[/list]
[line]
[size=5][color=#ffff00][b]How to Use[/b][/color][/size]
[list=1]
[*]Open the Cyber Engine Tweaks overlay.
[*]The "Relic Terminal Checklist" window will appear.
[*]Click the checkboxes to mark your progress manually, or let the [b]Proximity Scanner[/b] handle that for you.
[*][b]Proximity Scanning[/b]: Enable (default) this in the [b]Settings[/b] tab to see nearby items on your HUD as you play.
[list][*]You can adjust the detection range in the Settings tab (default 50m, adjustable from 25m to 100m). There is no scan interval to set; the scanner is event driven now.
[/list][/list][*]To save your progress, [b]Quicksave (F5)[/b] or [b]Manual Save[/b] your game. The progress is tied to that save file.
[line]
[size=5][color=#ffff00][b]Lazy Mode[/b][/color][/size]
For those who just want to get it done, you can enable "Lazy Mode" in the Settings tab. This will show the "Teleport" and "Unstuck" buttons.

[color=#e06666][b]WARNING:[/b][/color] Using teleport functions can be risky. It may cause issues with your save or get you stuck. Use at your own risk and always have a recent manual save!

[line]
[size=5][color=#ffff00][b]Requirements[/b][/color][/size]
[color=#e06666][b]0-Engine is a new required dependency. Versions before 3.0.0 did not need it. If 0-Engine is not installed the checklist will not run, and you will see a single error line in the CET log.[/b][/color]
[list]
[*][b][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/cyberpunk2077/mods/107]Cyber Engine Tweaks[/url][/b]
[*][b][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/cyberpunk2077/mods/27967]0-Engine[/url][/b] (the pure CET-only build, version 0.18.3 or newer). It has its own requirements, listed on its mod page.
[/list]
[line]
[size=5][color=#ffff00][b]Installation[/b][/color][/size]
[list=1]
[*]Install [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/cyberpunk2077/mods/27967]0-Engine[/url] and its requirements (above).
[*]Install this mod with a mod manager (recommended).
[*]For manual install, download and extract the main file into your Cyberpunk 2077 game directory.
[/list]
[line]
[size=5][color=#ffff00][b]Known Issues[/b][/color][/size]
[list]
[*]When you use the "Set Map Pin" button, the breadcrumbs (navigation path) may not appear immediately. You will need to [b]open and close your in-game Map (M)[/b] for the path to appear.
[/list]
[line]
